Updating the spotifyd.conf file takes only a few easy steps

1) go the the spotifyd.conf file   cd ~/.config/spotifyd

2) find your output device   aplay -L

Sample result:

[root@havana ~]# aplay -L

null
Discard all samples (playback) or generate zero samples (capture)
sysdefault:CARD=U20F1 <------USE THIS LINE
USB Audio 2.0(F1), USB Audio
Default Audio Device
front:CARD=U20F1,DEV=0
USB Audio 2.0(F1), USB Audio

3) open spotifyd.conf file  nano spotifyd.conf

4) use the 4-way arrows and backspace to find/replace the default with your information

5) afterward select ctrl + X to exit, then y to accept and enter....then type reboot

Done
